cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.DC 

This paper discusses incentive mechanisms for participatory sensing systems, which involve collecting data from users' smartphones. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including social and information networks (cs.SI), cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). However, given the focus on user incentives and participation, we believe that cs.SI and cs.HC are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CY, cs.CR, and cs.DC.
